Description: Fix CVE-2023-2976 - FileBackedOutputStream/createTempDir insecure permissions
 FileBackedOutputStream and Files.createTempDir relied on default OS permissions
 for temporary files/directories. This backport routes both through TempFileCreator,
 which uses java.nio.file with owner-only POSIX permissions on Unix and falls back
 on non-POSIX filesystems (e.g. Windows). Adapted from the 28.2-jre JRE-only
 backport: skips android flavor, root pom.xml, and the fragile upstream Android
 Path-detection path that always passed POSIX attributes.
Origin: upstream, https://github.com/google/guava/commit/feb83a1c8fd2e7670b244d5afd23cba5aca43284
Author: cpovirk <cpovirk@google.com>
Last-Update: 2026-07-21

